         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/8/76 ¶  ¶ Can you kindly ascertain for me, dear Mr. Ware, ¶  ¶ how ¶  ¶ many ¶  ¶ schools exist under the education Department, as I like to decide, how many copies of the School Flora ought to be ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.08.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Ware</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">J76/8600, unit 880, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence VA 475 Chief Secretary Department, Public Record office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/8/76</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Can you kindly ascertain for me, dear Mr. Ware,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">how</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">many</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>schools exist under the education Department, as I like to decide, how many copies of the School Flora ought to be printed.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The proposed work was aborted by the Chief Secretary; see Lucas et. al. (2009), pp. 37-9, and notes to M to J. MacPherson, 21 March 1876.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The third part of the educational collection can be sent in a few days; shall I forward the parcels to the office?<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A MS annotation in an unknown hand ran together the question about the proposed book and the collections of exsiccatae, 'Educational collections of Australian plants': 'The schools are several hundreds in number. The Schools at great centres are unlikely to fi</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">nd any use for botl specimens?</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">'</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 23 August the Under Secretary, W. Odgers, asked the Education Department 'to say how many copies of the School Flora' would be required, to which the Secretary of the Department, H. Venables, replied on 29 August: 'A circular on the subject has been issued to all the State Schools in Victoria &amp; when replies shall have been received I shall be able to say how many schools will be prepared to assist in the object in view'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">For the distribution of the exsiccatae to public libraries, a circular was sent to 49 public libraries,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">mechanics' institutes or the equivalent that had received Parts I and II of the collection,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">asking them to indicate if they wished to have Part III<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">No</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">. 2172, unit 42</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, pp. 1213-4</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">A file note records in alphabetical order the names of the 3</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">4</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>institutions to which a copy<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">of the new Part<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">was sent on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">8 November 1876<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Unit 43, p. 1129, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's, Public Record Office, Victoria</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">).</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>These are regrouped her</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by category</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">:</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mechanics institutes: Ararat, Avoca, Ballarat, Belfast (now Port Fairy), Camperdown, Castlemaine, Cheltenham, Creswick, Geelong, Heathcote, Kilmore, Portland, Prahran, Sale, Sandhurst (now Bendigo), Stawell, Taradale, Warrnambool, Williamstown.<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Libraries, variously described as 'public': Ballarat, Buninyong, Dunolly, Eaglehawk, Queenscliff, Richmond; 'free': Benalla, Clunes, Collingwood, Echuca, Maryborough; or 'free public': Beechworth.<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Athenaeums: Maldon, Stanley, Wangaratta.<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 22 November 1876,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a different hand recorded that a copy had also been sent to Kew Library and Institute.</p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
